Although, I think not having the wrapper make it less readable. What difference between GetCoins and AccessCoins ? if the problem was about performance, we could have used AccessCoins in the wrapper, it would spare us some code.

@CodeShark I'm not against squashing anything, I just thought it was better for review to keep th

@Nicolas there is a consensus rule that all transactions (including
coinbases) have at least one input and one output.

No opinion otherwise.

@sipa a rewrite has been done by #6898 makes it impossible to call LockTime by passing the prevHeights. (because all calls to the CCoinsView have been remove)
I have the feeling that fetching the prevHeights by using the view to fix the problem will kill the perf improvement made by #6898, making it irrrelevant.

